   <title>
    <narrative xml:lang="EN">D. Agricultural policy</narrative>
   </title>
   <description>
    <narrative xml:lang="EN">D.	Agricultural policy. In the DRC, agricultural law and many interventions in the agricultural sector tend to focus on large scale agriculture. There is need to address the needs and ambitions of small farmers to reduce poverty, but also the number of land conflicts related to large scale agricultural concessions. The programme will, through lobby and advocacy, influence the ongoing process of designing agricultural policies and strategies, with the objective to promote inclusive access to land of local land users and highlight the potential impact on stabilisation, peace, and security.</narrative>
   </description>
